  m_Name: Mushroom_19_Hollowheart
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.MushroomFieldGuideData
  _id: hollowheart
  _commonName: Hollowheart
  _latinName: Unrecorded
  _edibility: 4
  _edibilityLabel: "Unknown \u2014 old knowledge"
  _description: 'A rare fungus of the oldest stumps, named for where it grows: the hollowed heart of a tree that died before the village had its name. Sable''s drawing shows it half in shadow, as if the page itself were being careful.'
  _idFeatures:
  - Grows only inside hollow ancient stumps
  - Flesh darkens quickly when cut
  - Never more than a few to a stump
  _habitat: Hollow hearts of ancient stumps, Deep Wood
  _season: Unknown — the seedbook is silent
  _lookalikes: Any dark stump fungus, in bad light. The habitat is the identifier; nothing else lives where it lives.
  _notes: 'The seedbook pairs it with a warning in Sable''s hand that the damp has taken all but two words: ''… only once.'''
